= Admonitions

Admonitions are callout blocks that draw attention to important information.

== NOTE Admonition

NOTE: This is a note admonition. Use it to provide additional information that is helpful but not critical.

== TIP Admonition

TIP: This is a tip admonition. Use it to provide helpful hints or best practices.

== IMPORTANT Admonition

IMPORTANT: This is an important admonition. Use it to highlight critical information that users must be aware of.

== WARNING Admonition

WARNING: This is a warning admonition. Use it to alert users about potential problems or dangers.

== CAUTION Admonition

CAUTION: This is a caution admonition. Use it to warn users about actions that could cause problems.

== Admonition Blocks

Admonitions can also be used as blocks to contain multiple paragraphs or other content:

[NOTE]
====
This is a note block that can contain multiple paragraphs.

It can also contain lists:

* Item one
* Item two
* Item three

And even code blocks or other elements.
====

[WARNING]
====
This is a warning block with multiple paragraphs.

Use admonition blocks when you need to include complex content within an admonition.
====


